  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks to combat money laundering, including:\n\n1. International frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National level legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Report (SAR) mandates\n\n3. Key compliance mechanisms:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Enhanced screening of high-risk transactions\n\n4. Regulatory oversight:\n- Central banks\n- Financial regulatory agencies\n- Law enforcement collaboration\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\n5. Penalties for non-compliance:\n- Significant monetary fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Potential business license revocation\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions and financial sectors.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
